data.title: Archduchess Maria Caroline of Austria (1825
data.text:
Carte de visite photographs from an album including the Austrian Royal family and relatives together with various members of the Austrian Imperial court.

c 1862 - 1865.

Erzherzogin Maria Caroline von Ã–sterreich (1825-1915)

(Maria Caroline Luise Christine Habsburg-Teschen)

Daughter of Archduke Karl Ludwig of Austria and Henriette Alexandrine, Princess of Nassau-Weilburg.

In 1852 she married Archduke Rainer Ferdinand of Austria.

Cdv by Ludwig Angerer, Wien.
